No, 134 is decently challenging in its own right. The probability you use in 70 is too mechanical; it helps a bit but very little in 134, which is mostly theoretical. 53 will help for some parts (it's necessary for some) but not all and only really helps as a tool not a primary topic.

I think STAT 134 will be easy if you did well on the probability part of CS 70. CS 70 covers most of the Discrete Probability taught in 134, and a good portion of the continuous topics too.
